content:
It seems like your navbar is transparent because there is no background color set for it. To make the navbar not transparent, you can add a background color to the `.sticky-navbar` class in the CSS:
```css
.sticky-navbar {
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
  background-color: #f8f9fa; /* Add this line */
  padding: 10px 0;
}
```
This will set the background color of the navbar to a light gray color.

If you want the navbar to be transparent only when not scrolling, you can follow the solution I provided earlier in this conversation.
